cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.AI, cs.ST

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel method for learning a latent factor graphical model from temporal data using an information-theoretic objective function. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The proposed method optimizes an information-theoretic objective function to estimate the covariance structure of multivariate time series. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The method can be applied to analyze complex multivariate time series such as high-resolution fMRI data, which can be modeled as a network. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method can be used for detecting sudden changes in the underlying covariance matrix and capturing transient correlations, which are important tasks in many AI applications. 
- cs.ST (Statistics): The paper deals with the problem of estimating the covariance structure of multivariate time series, which is a fundamental problem in statistics.
